==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: onside kick
<hw>onside kick</hw> <fld>(Football)</fld> <def>A kickoff in which the
kicking team attempts to kick the ball only so far as is legally
required (beyond the 50-yard line), so as to have a better chance to
recover the kicked ball itself; -- it is a risky type of play used only
when the kicking team is losing and there is little time left to
play.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>on-site</ent>⟦br⟧
